  "prompt": "How do you clean a penny board?",
  "response": "Cleaning a penny board is a straightforward process. Here are the steps to help you clean it effectively:\n\n### Materials Needed\n- Mild soap or detergent\n- Water\n- Soft cloth or sponge\n- Toothbrush or soft-bristled brush\n- Bucket or basin (optional)\n- Towels\n\n### Steps to Clean Your Penny Board\n\n1. **Remove Accessories**: If your penny board has any removable accessories, such as stickers or grip tape, take them off if they are not waterproof.\n\n2. **Prepare Cleaning Solution**: Mix a mild soap or detergent with water in a bucket or basin. You can also use plain water if your board is not very dirty.\n\n3. **Wipe the Deck**:\n   - Dip the soft cloth or sponge into the cleaning solution and wring it out to avoid excessive water.\n   - Wipe down the deck of the penny board, paying special attention to any dirty or sticky areas. Avoid soaking the board, as excessive moisture could affect the integrity of the board.\n\n4. **Clean the Wheels**:\n   - Use a toothbrush or soft-bristled brush to clean around the wheels and on the wheel wells. This will help remove dirt and debris that may have accumulated.\n   - You can also remove the wheels if necessary (using a wrench) to clean them thoroughly.\n\n5. **Rinse (Optional)**: If you used soap, you can use a damp cloth to wipe away any soap residue. Make sure not to soak the board.\n\n6. **Dry**: Use a towel to dry the board and wheels thoroughly. Make sure there\u2019s no moisture left before reattaching wheels or putting any accessories back on.\n\n7. **Reassemble**: If you removed the wheels, reattach them securely. If you removed grip tape or stickers, reapply them as needed.\n\n### Additional Tips\n- Avoid using harsh chemicals or abrasive sponges as they might scratch the surface of the board or damage the grip tape.\n- Regularly cleaning your penny board will help maintain its appearance and performance.\n- Store your board in a dry place to prevent mold or mildew.\n\nFollowing these steps should help keep your penny board looking good and functioning well!",
